      "content": "interesting. so it sounds like the bill is pretty much a done deal then, since the transition is \"predictable.\" but if it's basically going to hurt these towns, why is it being framed as a \"necessary\" move? shouldn't there be a more balanced way to look at it if people's livelihoods are being tossed aside?",
